article.headline: Sam Houston State 81, Alcorn State 78
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Ryan Bright scored 29 points, including six in the final three minutes, and Sam Houston State beat Alcorn State 81-78 on Saturday. The Bearkats (5-3) led by as much as 16 in the first half and 11 at halftime after hitting eight 3-pointers in the first 10 minutes. But the Braves (0-8) rallied in the second half to cut to lead to 71-70 with about six minutes left and were within two points three times in the final two minutes. Aaron Wade scored 17 points for Sam Houston State, including five 3s, and Reggie Rawlins added 14. Delvin Thompson led Alcorn State with 21 points. Juan Wyatt added 15.
